  ANIMALS OF THE WORLD
============================================================

Name:         African Elephant
Scientific:   Loxodonta africana
Class:        Mammalia
Habitat:      Savanna
Diet:         Herbivore
Lifespan:     70 years
Weight:       6000 kg
Status:       Vulnerable
Fact:         Largest land animal; strongest sense of smell; mourns the dead

Name:         Hummingbird
Scientific:   Trochilidae
Class:        Aves
Habitat:      Forest
Diet:         Omnivore
Lifespan:     5 years
Weight:       0.003 kg
Status:       Varies
Fact:         Only bird that can fly backwards; heart beats 1,260 times per minute

Name:         Peregrine Falcon
Scientific:   Falco peregrinus
Class:        Aves
Habitat:      Cliffs/Cities
Diet:         Carnivore
Lifespan:     15 years
Weight:       1 kg
Status:       Least Concern
Fact:         Fastest animal on Earth at 389 km/h in a dive

============================================================
  FAMOUS PEOPLE
============================================================

Name:          Nelson Mandela
Lived:         1918 - 2013
Nationality:   South African
Field:         Politics
Known For:     End of apartheid
Contribution:  First democratically elected SA president; 27 years in prison; Nobel Peace Prize
Quote:         "Education is the most powerful weapon you can use to change the world."

Name:          Isaac Newton
Lived:         1643 - 1727
Nationality:   English
Field:         Physics/Math
Known For:     Laws of Motion, Gravity
Contribution:  Principia Mathematica; invented calculus; explained planetary motion
Quote:         "If I have seen further, it is by standing on the shoulders of giants."

Name:          Ada Lovelace
Lived:         1815 - 1852
Nationality:   English
Field:         Computing
Known For:     First computer algorithm
Contribution:  Wrote first algorithm for Babbage's machine; recognized computing potential
Quote:         "The Analytical Engine weaves algebraic patterns."

